1 SECTION 6. If a right with respect to property to which this act applies is acquired,
2 extinguished, or barred on the expiration of a limitation period that began to run under another
3 statute before the effective date of this act, that statute continues to apply to the right even if the
4 statute has been repealed or superseded by this act.
5 SECTION 7. This act becomes effective January 1, 2026. Except as provided in
6 Section 6 of this act, this act applies to a judicial proceeding commenced on or after that date,
7 regardless of the date of death of the decedent.
